question: Why do helicopter blades make the choppy sound they do when they are spinning around at a constant speed ? If they are turning at the same rate , should n't they just make sort of a buzzing sound and not a pulsing sound ? Explain like I'm five.
response:
When helicopter blades spin around at a constant speed, they create turbulence in the air that makes a choppy sound. The turbulence is caused by the blades pushing against each other and creating eddies of air that move back and forth. These eddies of air are what make the sound that you hear as the helicopter flies by. 

The reason why this sound is described as "choppy" is because it is not a continuous sound, but rather a series of short bursts of noise. This is because the blades are constantly changing their position relative to the airflow, causing the eddies to form in different places every time they rotate. As a result, the sound is not uniform and has a choppy quality to it.

question: What happens in the brain of a schizophrenic ? How is it different to a " normal " brain ? Explain like I'm five.
response:
The brain of a person with schizophrenia has some differences compared to a "normal" brain. In particular, there are often changes in the way that certain parts of the brain communicate with one another. For example, the communication between areas responsible for thinking and planning (the prefrontal cortex) may be impaired in someone with schizophrenia. This can lead to problems with organizing thoughts and making decisions. 

In addition, there may also be differences in how certain chemicals in the brain work. Chemical messengers called neurotransmitters are responsible for transmitting signals between neurons in the brain. In people with schizophrenia, there may be too much or too little of these messengers, which could affect how well messages get across from one part of the brain to another.

Overall, these changes in the way that certain parts of the brain communicate with one another and how certain chemicals function may contribute to some of the symptoms experienced by individuals with schizophrenia.

question: How does 2 - way glass work ? If light can go through one way why ca n't it go through the other way also ? edit : I think I mean one - way glass Please explain like I'm five.
response: Two-way glass works by having two layers of glass with a thin film of silver in between them. The silver is coated on the outside surface of each layer of glass and acts as a mirror. When light enters the glass from one side, it bounces off the silver layer and comes out the other side. When light enters from the opposite direction, it reflects off the first layer's silver coating and gets reflected back again before coming out the second layer's silver coating. So only light that enters from one side can pass through to the other side; light entering from the opposite direction will be reflected back out.

question: Please explain what is "Missing data"

question: What is the difference between 1080i and 1080p ? I 've been looking at TV 's recently , and noticed 1080p and 1080i , what exactly is the difference ? Which is better ? Explain like I'm five.

question: vegetable washing When fruits and verges are covered in pesticides , feces and e - coli these days how does rinsing under running water remove these dangerous things ? Please explain like I'm five.

The best way to ensure good hygiene when preparing food is by following these simple steps : 1) Wash your hands with soap and warm water for at least 20 seconds ; 2) Rinse the produce under cold running water ; 3) Peel away any visible dirt or skin ; 4) Cut off any damaged areas where there may be bacteria hiding ; 5) Use separate cutting boards and knives for raw meat vs. fruits & veggies ; 6) Store leftovers in sealed containers at room temperature until ready to eat again ; 7) Cook meats thoroughly until done through internal temperature checks ; 8) Serve hot foods immediately upon completion ; 9) Avoid cross contamination by keeping raw meats separate from other ingredients when cooking ; 10 ) Don’t forget about cleaning up all surfaces including countertops , appliances etc.. after preparing meals !

Some people produce more earwax than others due to genetics or environmental factors such as humidity levels. In order to reduce the amount of earwax produced, it's best to use over-the-counter products such as drops or sprays that contain ingredients like alcohol or hydrogen peroxide. question: The differences between classes and functions in programming . Bonus points for using python . Thanks for helping out a noob ! Explain like I'm five.
response:
class is a blueprint for creating objects while an object is an instance of a class . In order to create an object you must first define its class which will specify what attributes it has (i.e what properties it has ) as well as the methods that can be called on that object (i.e what operations can be performed on the object ). Once defined , you can then instantiate your class by calling its constructor method which creates an object from the class definition . The syntax used to define classes looks like this: class ClassName(object):  def __init__(self, arg1, arg2,... ):    self.arg1 = arg1    self.arg2 = arg2... # other code goes here
# end of class definition
def someMethod(self):    # implementation of some method goes here
  # end of method definition
class AnotherClass(object):
   def anotherMethod(self):
      # implementation of another method goes here
  # end of method definition
objectName = ClassName(arg1, arg2,... )
# instantiation of class
objectName.someMethod() 
# call someMethod on instantiated object
AnotherObject = AnotherClass()
AnotherObject.anotherMethod()
# call anotherMethod on instantiated object

question: Trickle down economics Can someone explain the theory behind trickle down economics ? what are the benefits and drawbacks of trickle down economics ? And does it actually work ? Explain like I'm five.
response: trickle down economics is when the government gives money to rich people so that they can give it back to the poor.  The idea is that if rich people have more money they will spend it on things that help the economy like buying houses or starting businesses which in turn helps everyone else.  This way everyone wins!  The benefits of this include increased wealth for those who get the money first (the rich) as well as economic growth for everyone else since their spending creates jobs and stimulates demand.  However there are some drawbacks too - if not enough people benefit from it then it could end up hurting instead of helping everyone in the long run.  It also assumes that giving money directly to rich people will somehow automatically translate into better outcomes for everyone else - but this isn't always true.  In short - it depends on how it's implemented but generally speaking it has both advantages and disadvantages depending on the situation.

In an alternate universe where people use S.A.D.M.E.P., they would do parentheses first, then subtracts, then multiplies and divides (from left to right) and finally adds and subtracts (from left to right). question: Why is it easier to balance yourself on a fast moving bicycle rather than a slow one ? How does the linear speed in one direction alter the weight distribution in another ? Please explain like I'm five.
response:
it's easier to balance yourself on a fast moving bicycle rather than a slow one because the fast moving bike has more momentum and therefore more weight.  This means that even if you are off balance, your body will still be able to correct itself quickly as the bike continues to move forward at a steady pace.  In contrast, when you're on a slower moving bike, any small change in your position can cause you to lose balance more easily since there isn't enough momentum for your body to correct itself quickly enough.
  
The linear speed in one direction also affects the weight distribution in another - as an example, imagine holding onto a pole while riding a bicycle: when you move forwards, your arms will naturally swing backwards, which will affect how much of your body weight is distributed over each leg.  If you were moving very slowly then this effect wouldn't be noticeable; however if you increase your speed then it becomes more noticeable how changing directions changes where your center of gravity is located relative to the ground.
